<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5350394>
    dc:description "Figs. 60–63. Features of male Augochlorini. 60. Labrum of Caenaugochlora (Caenaugochlora) costaricensis (Friese). 61. From left to right: apex of scape, pedicel, F1, F2, and basal margin of F3 for Corynura (Callistochlora) prothysteres (Vachal). 62. From bottom to top: scape, pedicel, F1, F2, F3, and basal margin of F4 for Pereirapis semiaurata (Spinola). 63. Distal flagellomeres of Pseudaugochlora graminea (Fabricius), F11 hooked at apex." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5350394/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

